Old copy and paste from a while back. Most of it still holds true but the match example I gave is a bit outdated (still a good match nonetheless).

Stardom is honestly your best bet if you want a wrestling promotion with quality matches AND an English speaking community. The only "problem" with Stardom is that the really high quality matches are saved for more important shows. So your average show features a bunch of Trios and 8-man tags, which can be pretty fun when people you like are involved, but usually get repetitive otherwise. If you've never seen any Stardom before, I recommend watching a video or two from Stardom's official playlist on YouTube. It's currently the only legal way to watch Stardom for free.
>https://www.youtube.com/playlist?list=PLCs8EA-kFD1j25a7wKaHNIFxuUHAqVArp

I think it's easier to get into if you find a specific worker you really like and watch matches involving them. As a QQ mark, I'd recommend giving Momo Watanabe a shot. She's really fun and bubbly out of the ring, but takes her job in the ring more serious than anyone else I've ever seen in Stardom. Her match against Mayu, the current Ace of Stardom, earlier this year was pretty great.
>https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=-ZM_ikd5bdw&list=PLCs8EA-kFD1j25a7wKaHNIFxuUHAqVArp&index=29&t=571s&ab_channel=STARDOMofficial
